1 Estimate range size of Eurasian beaver

Eurasian beaver (Castor fiber, Linnaeus, 1758)

1.1 Objective

1.2 Useful packages, functions, hints

library(raster) # handles raster data
library(sp)     # handles vector, polygon, and point data 
library(rgdal)  # handles geographic projections
library(rgeos)  # calculations with spatial data

Functions to check: raster, rasterize, aggregate, gArea, gConvexHull, SpatialPoints

Keywords to look for: coastline paradox, convex hull.

1.3 Data

Load the data

pts <- read.csv("data/beaver_points/beaver_points_equal_area.csv")

shp <- readOGR(dsn = "data/beaver_shapefile",
               layer = "beaver_shape_equal_area")
## OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile 
## Source: "data/beaver_shapefile", layer: "beaver_shape_equal_area"
## with 2 features
## It has 1 fields
borders <- readOGR(dsn = "data/global_boundaries",
               layer = "world_equal_area")
## OGR data source with driver: ESRI Shapefile 
## Source: "data/global_boundaries", layer: "world_equal_area"
## with 246 features
## It has 11 fields

Plot the data

plot(shp, col="pink")
points(pts, cex=0.1, col="red")
plot(borders, add=TRUE, border="grey")
